10/23/2022,748.2851(b) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,11/28/2022,11/22/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,No,Documentation provided stated the post discussion was held with the child and a staff that was not involved in the restraint.,"On November 22, 2022 an email was received from the Administrator stating the following: The following was sent to all supervisors concerning our deficiencies on this investigation.  We will also review this as a whole group at our next all-staff meeting.  I also met with our Quality Assurance Manager and reviewed the report and expectations for us as a facility moving forward.  
I understand that the child refused to have a post discussion with staff involved in the restraint, however, this should be noted in the restraint report.  For example:  Child refused to process incident with staff and requested to de-brief with Treatment Director.  Or, youth refused to debrief, staff will follow-up after a cooling off period. Then go back and complete the information the next day when youth was debriefed.   If the person(s) involved are able, they should always be the one(s) who debrief with youth and document youth's response.  
Please remind all staff that when a youth has a crisis, this is a teaching moment.  When everything has calmed down and the youth is able to regain control and be introduced back into the milieu, the teaching moment (debriefing) should be done.  Teaching our youth how to process crisis situations and discuss ways to handle future situations is vital to the success of our youths."
